You need two things: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` using `OnNavigating` + `GetDeferral()`, and `BackButtonBehavior` on the page. Here's the implementation:

**1. Custom "Cancel" back button on `EditProductPage.xaml`:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

**2. ViewModel with the back command and dirty tracking:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    bool hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    async Task Back()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!discard) return;
        }

        HasUnsavedChanges = false; // clear before navigating
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

**3. Guard the hardware/gesture back in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:**

This catches the Android back button and iOS swipe-back — cases where `BackButtonBehavior.Command` is *not* invoked:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();
        else
            vm.HasUnsavedChanges = false;

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `GetDeferral()` is required because the confirmation is `async` — without it the navigation completes before the dialog resolves.
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` handles taps on the Shell toolbar button; `OnNavigating` handles system back gestures.
- Set `HasUnsavedChanges = false` before allowing navigation so the guard doesn't fire a second time.
